Building Dropbox Nautilus Extension
--------------------------

To compile you'll need the following packages (or equivalent):

gnome-common
libtool
autoconf
automake1.9
autotools-dev
libnautilus-extension-dev
libnotify-dev

In the nautilus-dropbox directory just do:

$ ./autogen.sh
$ make
$ sudo make install

should be good.


Dropbox Linux on 64bit Ubuntu 8.04:
-------------------

You will need to install our custom python build:

$ sudo apt-get install libsqlite3-dev
$ hg clone ssh://$USER@turbo.getdropbox.com//var/hg/python-2.5-dropbox
$ cd python-2.5-dropbox
$ ./configure --prefix=$HOME/dropbox-python && make && make install # can't just do make install, python
  	      				       	       	    	    # build sucks

You will also need the dropbox client source (your probably already have it).
To start dropbox, In the client dir:

$ rm common_util/_librsync.so # not 64-bit, 64-bit version in binlib-ubuntu-8.04-amd64
$ PATH=$HOME/dropbox-python/bin:$PATH DBDEV=kindofmagic \
PYTHONPATH=./binlib-ubuntu-8.04-amd64/:./lib/ python dropbox.py

Once you have that started go into another terminal:

$ gnome-session-properties

now go to the "Current Session" tab and remove nautilus, then apply and close

$ export NAUTILUS_DEBUG=1
$ nautilus

Have fun!